org.tantalum

Class CancellationException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • org.tantalum.CancellationException

  • public class CancellationException
extends java.lang.Exception
    A queued Task had Task.cancel() called on it before it could complete execution. The return value of most tasks is not predictable and should not be used when this exception is thrown. Any chained tasks will have cancel() called to notify them that they will not be executed.

      Create an exception indicating the a Task has been explicitly cancel()ed
